              vs punishment blocks; (2) most were phasically excited by
              punishments; and (3) a subset was phasically excited by
              reward-predicting cues. By contrast, dopaminergic neurons did not
              show firing rate changes across blocks of trials. These results
              suggest that serotonergic neurons signal information about reward
              and punishment on multiple timescales.",
