  abstract = "Traditional rodent models of Pavlovian fear conditioning assess
              the strength of learning by quantifying freezing responses.
              However, sole reliance on this measure includes the de facto
              assumption that any locomotor activity reflects an absence of
              fear. Consequently, alternative expressions of associative
              learning are rarely considered. Here we identify a novel, active
              fear response ('darting') that occurs primarily in female rats.
              In females, darting exhibits the characteristics of a learned
